 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mt-6">Now that you have seen the top manufacturers, the next step is choosing the right partner for your specific needs. Here is a practical guide to making that decision.</p>
 </div>

 <section id="choosing" class="mb-16">
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200 shadow-sm">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">4. How to Choose the Right Power Bank Manufacturer?</h2>
 <div class="space-y-6 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
 <div>
 <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-brandBlue mb-2">1. Define Your Requirements First</h3>
 <p>Before you contact an OEM power bank supplier, know your target capacity (mAh), output power (W), battery type, certs needed, and target price. Product categories vary widely — from <a href="/products/power-bank/semi-solid-state/" class="text-brandOrange hover:underline">ultra-thin semi-solid-state models</a> to <a href="/products/power-bank/laptop-power/" class="text-brandOrange hover:underline">240W laptop power stations</a> — so define your product type before reaching out.</p>
 <div class="bg-brandBlue/5 border-l-4 border-brandOrange p-4 rounded-r-xl mt-4">
 <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm italic">"Sarah spent three months talking to a factory that claimed 20,000mAh capacity. After samples came, tests showed only 14,200mAh, a 29% gap. She switched to a maker with verified test reports and launched on time."</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 <div>
 <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-brandBlue mb-2">2. Verify Factory Credentials</h3>
 <p>Ask for ISO 9001 certs, CE/FCC test reports, and UN38.3 battery safety papers. Real factories should give these without delay.</p>
 </div>
 <div>
 <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-brandBlue mb-2">3. Check MOQ Alignment</h3>
 <p>Factory MOQ varies a lot, from 500 units (WOWOHCOOL, Allway) to 10,000+ (Anker). Pick a supplier whose MOQ fits your order size. Don't over-commit to high MOQs as a startup.</p>
 </div>
 <div>
 <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-brandBlue mb-2">4. Request Samples</h3>
 <p>Always order samples before bulk orders. A reliable maker will send samples in 3-7 days. Test charging speed, build quality, battery life, and cert claims.</p>
 </div>
 <div>
 <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-brandBlue mb-2">5. Evaluate R&D Capability</h3>
 <p>For custom ODM projects, make sure the maker has in-house engineers. Ask about their PCB design, tooling, and heat management skills.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 </div>
 </section>

